@startuml
title game-lib physics: worker bridge sequence

skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 160
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10
autonumber

box "Main thread" #E8F2FF
participant "Stage / Runtime" as Runtime
participant "ZylemWorld /\nStageEntityDelegate" as WorldLayer
participant "PhysicsProxy" as Proxy
participant "PhysicsBodyHandle" as Handle
collections "Queued BodyCommands" as Queue
end box

box "Shared contract" #F6F6F6
participant "physics-protocol" as Protocol
end box

box "Worker thread" #FFF4E0
participant "physics-worker" as Worker
participant "Rapier World" as Rapier
end box

box "Outbound notifications" #F3E8FF
participant "Collision listeners" as Collisions
end box

== Initialization ==

Runtime -> Proxy : init()
activate Proxy
Proxy -> Protocol : use message schema\nInit / Step / AddBody / RemoveBody
activate Protocol
Protocol --> Proxy : serializable contract ready
deactivate Protocol
Proxy -> Worker : spawn worker + post Init
activate Worker
Worker -> Rapier : create physics world
activate Rapier
Rapier --> Worker : world ready
deactivate Rapier
Worker --> Proxy : ready
deactivate Worker

note right of Proxy
PhysicsProxy owns the worker connection,
maps body IDs to handles, and applies
authoritative worker results back onto
main-thread snapshots.
end note

== Body registration ==

WorldLayer -> Proxy : addBody(bodyDesc, colliderDescs)
Proxy -> Protocol : encode AddBody payload
activate Protocol
Protocol --> Proxy : transferable message
deactivate Protocol
Proxy -> Worker : post AddBody
activate Worker
Worker -> Rapier : create rigid body\ncreate colliders
activate Rapier
Rapier --> Worker : body handle + initial state
deactivate Rapier
Worker --> Proxy : bodyCreated(id, initial pose)
deactivate Worker
Proxy -> Handle : create(id, initial snapshot)
activate Handle
Handle --> Proxy : handle ready
deactivate Handle
Proxy --> WorldLayer : PhysicsBodyHandle
deactivate Proxy

note over Handle
PhysicsBodyHandle is the main-thread façade.
It exposes reads for translation / rotation /
velocity and writes like setLinvel(),
setTranslation(), setRotation(), applyImpulse().
end note

== Per-frame step ==

group Local writes before stepping
  Runtime -> Handle : setLinvel(...) / applyImpulse(...)\nsetTranslation(...) / setRotation(...)
  activate Handle
  Handle -> Queue : enqueue BodyCommand(s)
  Handle -> Handle : update local snapshot\nfor low-latency reads
  deactivate Handle
end

Runtime -> Proxy : step(delta)
activate Proxy
Proxy -> Queue : drain queued commands
activate Queue
Queue --> Proxy : commands by body id
deactivate Queue

Proxy -> Protocol : encode Step message\n(commands + frame delta)
activate Protocol
Protocol --> Proxy : transferable payload
deactivate Protocol

Proxy -> Worker : post Step(...)
activate Worker
Worker -> Rapier : apply BodyCommands
activate Rapier
Worker -> Rapier : run fixed timestep loop
Worker -> Rapier : gather transforms + collisions
Rapier --> Worker : updated world state
deactivate Rapier

Worker -> Protocol : pack Float32Array transform buffer\n+ collision events
activate Protocol
Protocol --> Worker : stepResult payload
deactivate Protocol

Worker --> Proxy : stepResult(buffer, collisions)
deactivate Worker

Proxy -> Handle : apply authoritative state\nupdate interpolation history
activate Handle
Handle -> Handle : capture previous/current pose\nfor render interpolation
Handle --> Proxy : snapshots updated
deactivate Handle

Proxy --> Collisions : dispatch collision events
Proxy --> Runtime : frame state ready
deactivate Proxy

== Render/read phase ==

Runtime -> Handle : getRenderTranslation(alpha)\ngetRenderRotation(alpha)
activate Handle
Handle --> Runtime : interpolated pose
deactivate Handle

note over Runtime,Handle
Rendering and scene sync can read interpolated poses
from PhysicsBodyHandle while Rapier remains isolated
inside the worker.
end note

== Removal / teardown ==

WorldLayer -> Proxy : removeBody(id)
activate Proxy
Proxy -> Protocol : encode RemoveBody
activate Protocol
Protocol --> Proxy : payload
deactivate Protocol
Proxy -> Worker : post RemoveBody
activate Worker
Worker -> Rapier : remove rigid body / colliders
activate Rapier
Rapier --> Worker : removed
deactivate Rapier
Worker --> Proxy : removed(id)
deactivate Worker
Proxy -> Handle : invalidate snapshot
Proxy --> WorldLayer : body removed
deactivate Proxy

legend right
|= Element |= Responsibility |
| PhysicsProxy | main-thread bridge to the worker |
| PhysicsBodyHandle | cached read/write façade per body |
| physics-protocol | stable serializable message contract |
| physics-worker | worker-side runtime loop |
| Rapier World | authoritative physics simulation |
| Float32Array buffer | compact transform sync payload |
endlegend

@enduml
